commentary: Finn to Smith, 3 runs length ball, angling in towards middle stump. Smith makes it look like a bad ball by shuffling across and glancing towards the fine leg  boundary, but if he missed that, it was a sure lbw. Thing is, he simply doesn't miss, does he? He stays upright and makes sure his head isn't falling over
